","1293–Female":"1293–Deceased","about 1293":"about 1293","1316":"1316","1303":"1303","1373":"1373","1361":"1361","1293":"1293",",Hertfordshire,England.":"Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England":"Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Roger","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Philippe, Alcee, Armand, Laurent, Leonce, Marcel, Yves, Clovis, Fernand, Gilberte, Janvier, Jean Claude.","Scottish, English, North German, French, Walloon, Catalan, and West Indian (mainly Haiti): from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘renown’ +<i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear, lance’, which was introduced into England by the Normans in the form <i>Rog(i)er</i> and was reinforced by the Old Norse cognate <i>Hróthgeirr</i>.","History: Gabriel Roger from Sainte-Verge in Deux-Sèvres, France, married Marie (de) Lacour in Quebec City, QC, in 1669. — This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of South Carolina."],"variants":[{"name":"Rogero","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Cayetano, Jose, Silva.","Spanish: from the personal name <i>Rogero</i> (see   Roger  ).","Catalan (<b>Rogeró</b>): from a pet form of the personal name   Roger  ."]},{"name":"Rieck","meanings":["South German: from a pet form of the personal name <i>Ru(o)diger</i>, a compound of Old High German <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame, renown’ + <i>gēr</i> ‘spear, lance’ (see   Roger  ).","North German: from a short form of a personal name containing the element <i>rīc</i> ‘power(ful)’.","Germanized form of Sorbian <b>Rjek</b>: nickname from Upper Sorbian <i>rjek</i> ‘hero’. Compare   Reck  ."]},{"name":"Rogelio","meanings":["Spanish; Portuguese (<b>Rogélio</b>): from the personal name <i>Rogelio</i>, Portuguese <i>Rogélio</i>, of ancient Germanic origin (see   Roger  )."]},{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Roger  ."]},{"name":"Rogers","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Roger  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Irish: adopted for Gaelic <b>Mac Ruaidhrí</b> (see   Rorie  ).","History: Thomas Rogers (<i>c.</i> 1587–1621), born in London, England, was among the Pilgrim Fathers who sailed on the <i>Mayflower</i> in 1620. He died during the first winter at Plymouth Colony, but his son Joseph survived and married, and was later joined in MA by his brother John. This name was subsequently brought to North America independently by many different bearers."]},{"name":"Rogel","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jesus, Jose, Jose Luis, Juan, Marcos, Margarita, Wilfredo, Adilia, Alejandro, Ana Gladys, Ana Maria, Anacleto.","Spanish: from the personal name <i>Rogel</i>, an equivalent of French   Roger  .","Americanized form of Slovenian <b>Rogelj</b>: nickname or topographic name from <i>rogelj</i> ‘horn, point’, figuratively ‘tall young man’, as a topographic name probably denoting someone who lived e.g. on a horn-shaped spur of a hill. The surname in the form <i>Rogel</i> is found in Slovenia, too, where it is a less common variant."]},{"name":"Prosser","meanings":["Welsh: Anglicized form of Welsh <i>ap Rhosier</i> ‘son of Roger’ (see   Roger   and   Rosser  )."]},{"name":"Rogerson","meanings":["English: patronymic from the Middle English personal name   Roger   + <i>-son</i>."]},{"name":"Ritger","meanings":["Altered form of German and Dutch <b>Rutger</b> or <b>Rütger</b>, from the personal name <i>Rudiger</i> (see   Roger  )."]},{"name":"Rogge","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Otto, Bernd, Bernhard, Elke, Hans, Helmut, Wolfgang.","German and Dutch: from a short form of the personal name   Roger  .","North German and Dutch: metonymic occupational name for a grower of rye or a baker of rye bread, from Low German, Dutch <i>rogge</i> ‘rye’."]}]},{"name":"Isabella","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."],"variants":[{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabella Roger was born about 1293, in Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Earl Philip de Peletoyt."},"et":{"about 1293–":"umbes 1293–Surnud","1303–1361":"1303–1361","1316–1373":"1316–1373","1293–Female":"1293–Surnud","about 1293":"umbes 1293","1316":"1316","1303":"1303","1373":"1373","1361":"1361","1293":"1293",",Hertfordshire,England.":"Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England":"Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1293–":"noin 1293–Kuollut","1303–1361":"1303–1361","1316–1373":"1316–1373","1293–Female":"1293–Kuollut","about 1293":"noin 1293","1316":"1316","1303":"1303","1373":"1373","1361":"1361","1293":"1293",",Hertfordshire,England.":"Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England":"Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1293–":"environ 1293–Décédée","1303–1361":"1303–1361","1316–1373":"1316–1373","1293–Female":"1293–Décédée","about 1293":"environ 1293","1316":"1316","1303":"1303","1373":"1373","1361":"1361","1293":"1293",",Hertfordshire,England.":"Hertfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, England":"Watton at Stone, Hertfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Isabella Roger est née environ 1293, à Hertfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Earl Philip de Peletoyt."},"de":{"about 1293–":"um 1293–Verstorben","1303–1361":"13